        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>12 Upper Gower St</placeName>
                    <date>May 17<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1841</date>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I have the honour to transmit, as on former occasions, for the approval of the Lords Commissioners of Her Majesty’s Treasury the account of M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Smith and Elder for the third number of the Part 4. of the “Zoology of the Voyage of the Beagle”, which is now published.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I beg leave to state, that as before I have examined the account and superintended the expenditure of each part.</p>
<p>I have the honour to remain | Sir | Your obedient servant | Charles Darwin <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> To the | Secretary of the Treasury</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Preserved with this letter is an account from <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4407.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Smith, Elder &amp; Co</ref>., dated April 1841, detailing the various costs of <hi rend="italic">Fish,</hi> No. 3. The total expense was £37 1<hi rend="italic">s.</hi> 0<hi rend="italic">d.</hi></note>
        </div>        
            
